VALUES ('34fb689b-fc41-45e3-9c44-74a73f9d326f', 'Which choice completes the text so that it conforms to the conventions of Standard English?', 'Punctuation does quiet but decisive work at the seams of a sentence, signaling whether two ideas should be read as independent statements, as a cause joined to its effect, or as a main clause trailed by an explanatory aside; editors weigh these options carefully, and the sentence that follows presents exactly such a choice. The committee approved only one of the three proposals ______ the one that promised measurable results within a single fiscal year ______ and rejected the rest as too speculative.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":": ... :","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Comma Splice] Colons cannot wrap a mid-clause appositive."},{"id":"B","text":", ... ;","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Run-on Conjunction] Comma-semicolon pairing is unmatched."},{"id":"C","text":"— ... ,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Fragmented Semicolon/Colon] Dash-comma pairing is unmatched."},{"id":"D","text":"— ... —","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct (D). Matched em dashes set off the appositive."}]'::jsonb, 'D', 'Step 1 — Locate clause boundaries
